  "prompt": "Is the test taker report for GMAT accessible immediately after the test ? It\u2019s not the official score report that GMAC sends after 15-20 days.",
  "response": "Yes, the unofficial score report for the GMAT is available immediately after you complete the test. This report includes your scores for the Quantitative, Verbal, Integrated Reasoning sections, and the Total score. However, it does not include the Analytical Writing Assessment (AWA) score, as that section is graded separately. The unofficial score report allows you to see your performance right away, and you can decide to either accept or cancel your scores at that point. The official score report, which includes the AWA score and is sent to the schools you select, is typically available within 15-20 days after the test.",
